  "text": "Adult neurogenesis consists of different stages starting by the proliferation of type B cells (astrocytes) that then differentiate into DCXϩ cells and mature turning into functional neurons [CITATION_1] . Thus, we tested the expression of the transgene in the different stages that characterize the process (Fig. 3) . Using Ki67 antibody, which labels dividing cells, we demonstrated that ␤-gal expression colocalizes with Ki67 ( Fig. 3, A-C) . This fact shows that GSK3␤ transgene expression remains in dividing cells in the SGZ. We also checked a more mature state in the neurogenic process. We used DCX antibody for neuroblast labeling. No colocalization between ␤-gal protein and DCX was seen ( Fig. 3, D-F ). Finally, we tested whether transgene was expressed in mature granule cells using NeuN antibody. Positive cells for ␤-gal antibody did not express NeuN marker (Fig.  3, G-I) . These data suggest that exogenous GSK3␤ is expressed in dividing cells located in the SGZ and does not remain during the neuron's lifetime.",
